The paper deals with the capacity of communication channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the concept of anonymity, which is related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of correlated randomness suggests a possible connection to distributed systems (cs.DS) or networked information systems (cs.NI). Finally, the problem of anonymous communication may have applications in social networks or online privacy (cs.SI).
